author: Daniel Greene
description:
Audible is officially giving publishers access to its powerful AI narration tools, marking a major shift in the audiobook industry. In this video, I break down what this move means for authors, narrators, indie publishers, and listeners. Will this democratize audiobook creation, or threaten human narration jobs? How good is Audible’s AI tech really? Let’s dig into the potential impacts—both promising and concerning.
